  "bio_raw": "Dil Afroz Jahan is working as a lecturer at University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB). Her academic credentials include M.A & B.A. in History from University of Dhaka, Bangladesh. She also earned his second Masters’ degree in Governance and Development Studies in Jahangirnagar University, Bangladesh. Dil Afroz Jahan has also worked as Researcher at some renowned organizations like Save the Children, Plan International Bangladesh, Research and Development Collectives (RDC) and Association of Development agencies in Bangladesh (ADAB). She also worked at Somoy Television as a Newsroom Editor and Reporter. Prior to joining ULAB, she served as a Lecturer at Primeasia University.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Gender studies, communication, Sustainable Development, History, culture and sports."
  ],
